-- Russian Sugar-Beet Sowing Reaches 18% of Goal, Institute Says
-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 2012-04-23T14:55:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-23/russian-sugar-beet-sowing-reaches-18-of-goal-institute-says.html
Russian sugar-beet sowing reached
213,000 hectares (526,334 acres), about 18 percent of the
targeted area for the year, the Institute for Agricultural
Market Studies  said .  Planting increased by 43,100 hectares from a year earlier,
the Moscow-based institute, known as Ikar, said today on its
website. Ikar cited Agriculture Ministry figures for April 18.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow at 
 msysoyeva@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
